---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'healthcare-system', text: 'Healthcare System', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-requirements', text: 'Visa Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'insurance-requirements', text: 'Insurance Requirements', level: 2 },
  { id: 'recommended-providers', text: 'Recommended Providers', level: 2 },
  { id: 'costs', text: 'Expected Costs', level: 2 },
  { id: 'scenarios', text: 'Real-World Scenarios', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Antigua Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/antigua-and-barbuda/insurance' },
  { title: 'Insurance for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors' },
  { title: 'Bahamas for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/bahamas' },
  { title: 'Barbados for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/barbados' },
  { title: 'Jamaica for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/jamaica' },
];

const providerColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'entryAge', header: 'Max Entry Age' },
  { key: 'renewal', header: 'Renewal' },
  { key: 'monthlyFrom', header: 'From (65-69)' },
  { key: 'antiguaFit', header: 'Antigua Fit' },
];

const providerRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'XCD$1,350-1,930/mo', antiguaFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'BUPA Global', entryAge: '79', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'XCD$1,580-2,255/mo', antiguaFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'XCD$1,215-1,735/mo', antiguaFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'GeoBlue', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'XCD$1,130-1,615/mo', antiguaFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Local (Sagicor)', entryAge: '65', renewal: 'Varies', monthlyFrom: 'XCD$400-800/mo', antiguaFit: 'Limited' },
];

const costColumns = [
  { key: 'category', header: 'Expense' },
  { key: 'monthly', header: 'Monthly' },
  { key: 'annual', header: 'Annual' },
];

const costRows = [
  { category: 'International Insurance (65-69)', monthly: 'XCD$1,215-1,930', annual: 'XCD$14,580-23,160' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (70-74)', monthly: 'XCD$1,665-2,575', annual: 'XCD$19,980-30,900' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (75-79)', monthly: 'XCD$2,240-3,450', annual: 'XCD$26,880-41,400' },
  { category: 'Private Hospital Visit', monthly: 'XCD$300-600/visit', annual: 'As needed' },
  { category: 'Medical Evacuation', monthly: 'N/A', annual: 'XCD$50,000-150,000' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Seniors in Antigua and Barbuda 2026 | Retirement Guide"
  description="Guide to health insurance for seniors in Antigua and Barbuda. 365 beaches, Caribbean luxury, citizenship by investment, and coverage for retirees 65+."
  headline="Health Insurance for Seniors in Antigua and Barbuda"
  subheadline="Antigua and Barbuda offers 365 beaches, English-speaking Caribbean, luxury resorts, citizenship by investment, and sailing paradise—a premium Caribbean destination for wealthy retirees."
  heroImage="/images/countries/antigua-and-barbuda-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Senior Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Why Seniors Choose Antigua and Barbuda</h2>
  <p>
    Antigua and Barbuda offers 365 beaches (one for each day), English-speaking environment, strong British heritage, world-class sailing (English Harbour, Antigua Sailing Week), and citizenship by investment program. For affluent retirees seeking Caribbean luxury with tax advantages, Antigua provides premium beach lifestyle.
  </p>

  <p>
    St. John's is the capital with main services. English Harbour area offers historic Nelson's Dockyard. Jolly Harbour is popular expat community. Barbuda is quieter sister island. Population ~100,000. Miami is 3.5 hours by flight for medical backup.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts for Seniors</h3>
    <ul class="text-primary-800 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> Limited locally; Miami evacuation common</li>
      <li><strong>Language:</strong> English</li>
      <li><strong>Cost of Living:</strong> XCD$8,000-15,000/month (~$3,000-5,500 USD); expensive</li>
      <li><strong>Climate:</strong> Tropical; warm year-round; hurricane season</li>
      <li><strong>Character:</strong> Relaxed; sailing; luxury focused</li>
      <li><strong>Tax:</strong> No income tax on foreign income</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="healthcare-system">Antigua Healthcare System</h2>
  <p>
    Antigua healthcare is limited—Mount St. John's Medical Centre is main public hospital. Some private clinics for routine care. Limited specialists. Complex conditions require evacuation to Miami (3.5 hours), Puerto Rico (1.5 hours), or Martinique. International insurance with strong evacuation coverage essential.
  </p>

  <p>
    Private healthcare handles routine needs. Dental care available. Public system basic. For anything serious, evacuation is standard practice. Don't rely on local healthcare for complex senior conditions.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">Medical Evacuation Essential</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800 mb-0">
      Antigua cannot treat many complex conditions. Miami has world-class hospitals (Jackson Memorial, Baptist Health). Puerto Rico is closer (1.5 hours). International insurance with evacuation coverage is non-negotiable for seniors.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-requirements">Visa Options for Seniors</h2>
  <p>
    Antigua offers flexible residency options:
  </p>

  <h3>Citizenship by Investment</h3>
  <p>
    $100,000+ donation or $200,000+ real estate investment. Includes passport with visa-free travel to 150+ countries. Popular with wealthy retirees seeking global mobility.
  </p>

  <h3>Permanent Residency</h3>
  <p>
    Available through investment (lower threshold than citizenship) or after extended residence. Provides right to live without working.
  </p>

  <h3>Extended Stay Visa</h3>
  <p>
    For those not pursuing residency. Renewable stays. Good for testing the waters.
  </p>

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements">Insurance Requirements</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance requirements for Antigua:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Entry:</strong> Travel insurance strongly recommended</li>
    <li><strong>Residency:</strong> International coverage essential</li>
    <li><strong>Evacuation:</strong> Miami/Puerto Rico coverage critical</li>
    <li><strong>Hurricane:</strong> Consider evacuation during season</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Insurance Strategy for Antigua</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      Comprehensive international insurance with Miami/US evacuation essential. Local care handles routine needs. Include hurricane evacuation consideration. US hospital network access crucial given Antigua's medical limitations.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
  <p>
    For seniors in Antigua, US evacuation coverage critical:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

  <h3>Why These Providers Work for Antigua</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Strong Americas network, US access</li>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> Highest entry age (79), comprehensive</li>
    <li><strong>GeoBlue:</strong> US focus with Caribbean coverage</li>
    <li><strong>Miami access:</strong> World-class hospitals 3.5 hours away</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Get Personalized Senior Quotes</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Compare coverage for Antigua with US evacuation.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance costs for Antigua (XCD ~2.7 to USD):
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Cost-Saving Strategies</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>US access:</strong> Essential for complex care</li>
    <li><strong>Routine local:</strong> Private clinics affordable</li>
    <li><strong>Hurricane season:</strong> Consider evacuation coverage</li>
    <li><strong>Tax advantages:</strong> No income tax on foreign income</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: Sailing Retiree, 68</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $6,000/month income. English Harbour base. Yacht lifestyle.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Cigna Global with US/Caribbean coverage.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~XCD$1,500/month (~$555). Sailing paradise; Miami backup.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: CBI Passport Holder, 72</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $8,000/month. Citizenship by investment. Jolly Harbour villa.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> BUPA Global worldwide.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~XCD$2,000/month (~$740). Global mobility; premium coverage.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: Beach Lover, 66</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $4,500/month pension. St. John's area. Beach focused.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Allianz Care with Americas coverage.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~XCD$1,300/month (~$480). Beach lifestyle; essential backup.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is citizenship by investment worth it?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        For some—$100,000+ investment provides Antigua passport with 150+ visa-free destinations. Useful for travel. Not necessary for simple retirement residency. Popular with those seeking global mobility.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What about hurricanes?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Real risk—hurricane season June-November. Barbuda was devastated by Hurricane Irma (2017). Proper construction matters. Many expats leave during peak season (Aug-Oct). Insurance should cover hurricane evacuation.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Antigua expensive?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Yes—most items imported. Groceries expensive. Housing expensive in desirable areas. Budget $3,000-5,500/month for comfortable retirement. No income tax helps. Luxury Caribbean pricing.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Why choose Antigua over Barbados?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Better beaches (365 vs fewer). Stronger sailing culture. CBI program available. Less developed/commercial than Barbados. Smaller expat community. Barbados has better healthcare locally. Personal preference.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Ready to Compare Options?</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Get quotes from providers for Antigua coverage.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Healthcare in Antigua is limited—evacuation coverage essential. Hurricane preparedness important. Always verify current requirements with Antigua authorities.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
